    exact ‚ü®‚ü®_, ‚ü®n, rfl‚ü©‚ü©, hn‚ü©

/-- In a `p ^ ‚ąě`-torsion module (that is, a module where all elements are cancelled by scalar
multiplication by some power of `p`), the smallest `n` such that `p ^ n ‚ÄĘ x = 0`. -/
def pOrder {p : R} (hM : IsTorsion' M <| Submonoid.powers p) (x : M)
    [‚ąÄ n : ‚Ąē, Decidable (p ^ n ‚ÄĘ x = 0)] :=
  Nat.find <| (isTorsion'_powers_iff p).mp hM x

